div.div: A new life begins for Kitahara Iori as he begins his college career near the ocean in Izu city, full of excitement for his new life. He will be moving into his Uncle's diving store "Grand Blue." There he finds the beautiful ocean, beautiful women, and men that love diving and alcohol. Will Iori be able to live his dream college life?

An original anime series set in in the universe of Cyberpunk 2077. Cyberpunk: Edgerunners tells a standalone, 10-episode story about a street kid trying to survive in a technology and body modification-obsessed city of the future. Having everything to lose, he chooses to stay alive by becoming an edgerunnera mercenary outlaw also known as a cyberpunk. (Source: CD PROJEKT RED) Note: The first episode received a pre-screening at Anime Expo on July 2, 2022. The first 3 dubbed episodes were streamed on Twitch as part of a co-stream promotion on September 12, a day before the shows premiere.
Comedy, Drama, Mystery, Psychological, Romance, Supernatural

First season of the Monogatari Series, part 1/6. Contains the arcs Hitagi Crab, Mayoi Snail, Suruga Monkey, Nadeko Snake, and Tsubasa Cat from the Bakemonogatari light novels. Thanks to Meme Oshino, Koyomi Araragi, a high school student, is able to remain a human after coming across a female vampire... However, since the incident, Koyomi seems to meet girls who have an apparition-related issue. Hitagi Senjougahara doesnt weigh anything, Suruga Kanbarus right arm becomes like that of a monkeys, and a young girl, Mayoi, cannot find her way home no matter how many times she tries. Koyomi, a Mr. Nice Guy, ends up helping each and every girl solve her problem with the help of Meme Oshino.
(Source: Aniplex)

A man working a job far removed from his childhood dreams gets wrapped up in an unexpected situation! Becoming a monster, he aims once again to fulfill his lifelong dream! (Source: MANGA Plus) Note: - Nominated for the 14thManga Taisho Award in 2021. - Winner of the 7th Next Manga Award in the Web Manga Category in 2021.

"In Manchuria, human life is worthless"

The year was Showa 12 (1937). Isamu Hinata, a soldier of the Kanto Army, arrived in Manchuria and lost his right eye on the battlefield. Deemed useless, he was reassigned to the agricultural corps, producing food for the army, while enduring daily abuse from his superiors. One day, he discovered poppies the raw material for the narcotic opium being cultivated in a corner of the farm. To help save his sick mother, Isamu began to refine opium. This fateful decision would set in motion events that would change both his own destiny and that of Manchuria itself

(Source: Comic Days, translated)
